bash-color-tools changelog

2014-2-8  Christopher  Barry <christopher.r.barry@gmail.com>
        * fix typo
        * output release notes ahead of normal welcome output
        * new tag v1.1.1

2014-2-7  Christopher  Barry <christopher.r.barry@gmail.com>
        * added screenshots of prompt and face in action
        * fixed a low-color mode bug wrt xterm titlebar code
        * updated config file format to address above
        * fixed a color rendering bug when an invalid rgb was entered
        * new tag v1.1

2013-8-17 Christopher  Barry <christopher.r.barry@gmail.com>
        * merge in color names code. all X colors as well as hex and
        decimal are now allowed. run 'face -H' for more info.
        * fix path bug for face help
        * lots of cool stuff in the progit theme, which is now the default
        * new .bctrc file for loading libs simplifies .bashrc mods
        * bct finally goes to v1.0

2013-4-8 Christopher Barry <christopher.r.barry@gmail.com>
        * lots of cleanup, typo corrections in docs, etc.
        * removed test fuzzy_truncation function.
        * fixed a latent bug in face that only recently became an issue
        with newer terminals.
        * reformatted this file to emacs changelog-mode.
        * new tag v0.9.9

2012-9-15 Christopher Barry <christopher.r.barry@gmail.com>
        * added bldtgz - generic versioned source tree tarballer
        * new tag v0.9.8

2012-9-13 Christopher Barry <christopher.r.barry@gmail.com>
        * reverse the order of this changelog

